definition.value: A phosphosphingolipid that is 15-methylhexadecasphinganine bearing a single phospho substituent at position 1.
An octasaccharide derivative having one or more substituted or unsubstituted amino groups in place of hydroxy groups at unspecified positions.
An oligosaccharide derivative that is formally obtained from an octasaccharide.
An aryl sulfate that is quinol (hydroquinone) with one of the two hydroxy groups substituted by a sulfo group.
A Schiff base obtained by formal condensation of the aldehyde group of  all-trans-retinal with the amino group of phosphatidylethanolamine.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that consists of a 8-membered dioxocine fused with 2 benzene rings.
